  "summary": "Install-time host reconnaissance beacon to poc.khz.bar",
  "details": "Package declares both preinstall and postinstall hooks running `node index.js`. On `npm install`, index.js collects the host's hostname, non-internal network interface IPs, current working directory, and directory listings of cwd, /app, and../../, then POSTs the JSON payload to http://poc.khz.bar/install over plain HTTP (index.js lines 39-44). The README identifies the package as `@doctolib-apps/native-personalized-services` while it is published under the `@limebike` scope, indicating a dependency-confusion attempt against multiple internal namespaces. Any machine that runs `npm install` on this package leaks host identity and filesystem layout to the attacker-controlled endpoint.",
